Kim Miller, Ph.D., is the District Manager at WellQor for New York, New Jersey, and Connecticut.   Dr. Miller is responsible for administering and interpreting psychological test data and providing psychotherapy to a geriatric population. She manages clinicians in the region, providing supervision and support when necessary. 

Dr. Miller is a licensed clinical psychologist with more than 20 years of experience leveraging assessment tools across a variety of areas. With a dual focus on clinical psychology and neuropsychology, she has administered psychodiagnostic and neuropsychological assessments to adults and children in both hospital and private practice settings and has provided psychotherapy to an adult population.

Prior to joining WellQor, Dr. Miller was a senior manager in the Search Assessment Practice at Korn Ferry, one of the world leading talent assessment and development firms in the world.  She was responsible for administering and interpreting Korn Ferry’s proprietary Search Assessment tools, as well as developing job and culture profiles used to benchmark candidates. She also focused on maximizing the use of assessment in all executive engagements firmwide and conducts executive feedback sessions.
 
Prior to her work at Korn Ferry, Dr. Miller was an Assistant Director of Hospitals at Kings County Hospital Center in Brooklyn, NY.  She served as the Director of Neuropsychological Services and Director of Adult Externship Training.  She was responsible for creating and directing the Behavioral Support Team, a consulting team designed to assist psychiatric inpatient units in effectively managing with patients with behavioral problems using a positive behavior support model.

Dr. Miller earned a bachelor’s degree in marketing from Hofstra University, a master’s degree in counseling and community psychology from Marist College, and a doctoral degree in clinical psychology from St. John’s University, with a specialization in Neuropsychological Assessment. She teaches introductory and abnormal psychology courses at the undergraduate level at Farmingdale State College and has taught similar courses at St. John’s University. Dr. Miller maintains a small private practice in neuropsychological assessment in New York City.

Linda Zacharias, MSW, LCSW is a clinician for WellQor, the nation’s leading provider of behavioral health services for Seniors. She has been working with WellQor for over two years and has learned and applied so much through the training offered through WellQor as she works with seniors and their family. Linda received her MSW at University of Wisconsin - Milwaukee in 2006. Since then, she was a case manager for people with chronic and pervasive mental health issues for 6 years and 8 years as a therapist in outpatient mental health clinics. Prior to going back to school for her Master’s, Linda was a missionary with Youth With A Mission (YWAM) for over ten years. Six of those years, Linda served in YWAM’s College of Counseling and Health Care and served in the U.S., Ukraine, Taiwan, Cambodia and other countries.

Linda has been successful in treating people for anxiety, depression, various traumas, bipolar, relationship issues and helping people through times of change such as, death of a loved one or adjusting to a new environment. Linda has taken many courses regarding nutrition and how it can effect the well being of a person and has recently taken courses on sleep issues and what causes a lack of sleep and what to do about it.    

Linda’s counseling philosophy is to reach the whole person - spirit, soul and body.
